close_reason: "Delivered typed Monica server infrastructure diagnostics with exact upstream research, version reconciliation, and read-only production-instance proof."
body: "## Problem\n\nThe maintained Monica 4.x route inventory is already fully mapped, but live read-only research against the configured self-hosted instance returns HTTP 500 with `Failed to load trust proxies from Cloudflare server.` The CLI currently reduces this Monica-originated infrastructure failure to generic retry advice, so humans and agents cannot distinguish an instance configuration/dependency problem from a transient API failure.\n\n## Research basis\n\n- The checked-in 35-resource, 172-endpoint snapshot matches `monicahq/monica` branch `4.x` commit `32028ce3ce79cef38df5d27a297e5b20680f0065`.\n- The error originates in `monicahq/laravel-cloudflare` when Monica cannot fetch Cloudflare IPv4/IPv6 proxy ranges.\n- The configured instance is kept in global private settings with read-only mode enabled; no production records may be mutated.\n\n## Delivery scope\n\nAdd a typed, reusable server-diagnostic classifier; expose stable diagnostic codes and operator actions in connection doctor and capability reports; retain the original safe error message; document the diagnostic contract and self-hosted remediation; validate all output schemas, help, unit, coverage, source-quality, and actual read-only CLI paths.\n\n## Non-goals\n\nDo not modify Monica records, change the Monica server, expose credentials, or invent route families beyond the maintained 4.x source."
